@startuml SCRUM-63 Seller Profile

title Buyer View Seller Profile (SCRUM-63)\n(public ratings · paginated reviews · active listings)

actor Buyer as B
participant "Browser\n(seller-profile.jsp)" as UI
participant "SellerProfileServlet\nGET /seller/{id}" as S
participant "SellerProfileDAO" as DAO
database "PostgreSQL\n(users · user_reviews · auction)" as DB

B -> UI : Navigate to /seller/42
UI -> S : GET /seller/42?page=1&size=10

activate S

note right of S
  <b>SCRUM-357 – Security:</b>
  • Public access — no session required
  • sellerId parsed from pathInfo as long
     non-numeric → HTTP 400
  • Only role_id = SELLER + status = Active
     returned by DAO; buyer/admin → HTTP 404
  • Email masked via SecurityUtil.maskEmail()
  • No password, phone_encrypted, address, 2FA loaded
end note

S -> S : parseSellerId(pathInfo) → 42
S -> DAO : getPublicProfile(42)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB : SELECT u.username, u.email, u.date_created,\n  profile_image_url, active_listings subquery\n  FROM users u WHERE id=? AND role_id=SELLER AND status=Active
DB --> DAO : seller row (or none)
DAO --> S : SellerPublicProfile (email pre-masked)
deactivate DAO

alt not an active seller
  S -> B : HTTP 404 Seller not found
else seller found
  S -> DAO : getAvgRating(42)
  activate DAO
  DAO -> DB : SELECT AVG(rating), COUNT(*) FROM user_reviews\n  WHERE reviewee_user_id = ?
  DB --> DAO : avg + count
  DAO --> S : AvgRating
  deactivate DAO

  S -> DAO : getReviews(42, page=1, size=10)
  activate DAO
  DAO -> DB : SELECT rating, comment, created_at, masked reviewer,\n  item_title FROM user_reviews …\n  ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 10 OFFSET 0
  DB --> DAO : review rows
  DAO --> S : List<ProfileReviewRow>
  deactivate DAO

  S -> S : set attrs: profile, avgRating, reviewCount,\n  reviews, pagination, reviewsEmpty
  S -> UI : forward seller-profile.jsp
  deactivate S
  UI -> B : Render seller info, ★ rating, active listings,\n  paginated review history with timestamps
end

== Invalid seller ID ==

B -> S : GET /seller/not-a-number
S -> S : parseSellerId → NumberFormatException
S -> B : HTTP 400 Invalid seller ID

== Non-seller user ==

B -> S : GET /seller/99  (user 99 is a Buyer)
S -> DAO : getPublicProfile(99)
DAO -> DB : SELECT … WHERE role_id = SELLER → no row
DAO --> S : null
S -> B : HTTP 404 (no role information leaked)

@enduml
